    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.00/17.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In practical compliance with Department’s September 22, 4 p.m., I addressed two
                    notes to the Foreign Office, one calling attention to the insistent rumor
                    relative to the views of the President of the Commission and stating that if
                    these views were shared by a majority of the Commission my Government would
                    regretfully feel compelled to advise American claimants not to resort thereto.
                    To this note the Foreign Office has replied that it will investigate the report,
                    but that the alleged views of the Commission’s President were not in any event
                    shared by the Government.</p>
                <pb facs="1059" n="943" xml:id="pg_943"/>
                <p>My second note requested an extension of time for filing claims to November
                    first. The Foreign Office replies that the Government is disposed to grant this
                    request and will give the Embassy a definite answer soon.</p>
                <p>The Commission has recently been increased by two reputable members, which seems
                    to increase confidence in it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
